examples.en: The Dean adjudicates any faculty disputes.
The court was set up to mediate in civil disputes.
They agree to litigate all disputes in this court.
The coal industry was plagued by industrial disputes.
The Commission will have the power to decide disputes.
The company has no effective machinery for resolving disputes.
Last year 1.3 million workers took part in industrial disputes.
They signed a treaty to settle all border disputes by arbitration.
Many trade disputes are pending, awaiting the outcome of the talks.
The mayor will act as the final arbiter in any disputes between board members.
The dean of student affairs is the proper arbiter when a student disputes a grade.
The pacific temper seeks to settle disputes on grounds of justice rather than by force.
In our family disputes regarding the use of our home entertainment system are umpired by Dad.
